Cambodian King Sends Large Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihamoni, King of Cambodia, sent a large floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh to celebrate the 58th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Written on the ribbons were letters "Congratulations on the 58th anniversary of the DPRK. King of Cambodia Norodom Sihamoni".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Authorized by the King, the secretary of State for the Royal Palace, together with under secretaries of State visited the embassy on September 8 to place the floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and make a bow. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary of State said that the King wished Kim Jong Il, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, Chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, good health and greater success in his noble work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The King warmly congratulated the anniversary and expressed the expectation that the traditional relations of friendship between the two countries would be everlasting, the secretary added.

Great King of Cambodia Sends Large Floral Basket to DPRK Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Norodom Sihanouk, Great King of Cambodia, sent a large floral basket to the DPRK embassy in Phnom Penh on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 Written on its ribbon were letters "Congratulations on the 58th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. Norodom Sihanouk, Great King of Cambodia".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Authorized by the Great King, the secretary of State for the Royal Palace, together with under secretaries of State paid a congratulatory visit to the embassy on September 8. They placed the floral basket before the portraits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and paid tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary of State said that the Great King and the Great Queen wished Kim Jong Il, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, Chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army, good health and greater success in his noble work.

Many Scientific and Technological Books Off Press 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The Central Scientific and Technological Information Agency published a lot of scientific and technological books of 250 kinds and electronic publications this year.
 Among them are books "The trend of the development of education in different countries" (4 volumes), "The outbreak and prevention of bird flu", "Chlorine dioxide and its use", "Multilingual materials for study of IT " conducive to developing science and technology of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Particularly, information scientific and technological magazines "Information science and technology", "Nano science and technology" and "Computer and program technology" are substantially helpful to the technical improvement and production of different sectors of the national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agency produced many CDs of scientific and technological data from this year to open a sure vista to improve the dissemination of science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its group of experts in programming produced electronic publications "Technology of cultivating potatoes with no virus", "Technology of cultivating cucumbers", "Technology of repairing automobiles easy for all to learn", "Massage treatment" and other scientific and technological data and materials for study of foreign languages with vivid screen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agency issued in time "News of current technology," "Data on the trend of the development of global science and technology" and other information publications for rapid and correct dissemination of the latest scientific and technological data.

Sixth National Sports Meet of Agricultural Workers Closes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The Sixth National Sports Meet of Agricultural Workers opened at the Rungrado Recreation Ground in Pyongyang on Sept. 7 on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK closed on Monday.
 The sports meet, participated in by more than 400 agricultural workers selected from provincial contests, included Taekwon-Do, Yut-game, Korean wrestling, swinging and seesaw. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Players of the Jongbang Co-op Farm in Sariwon City, North Hwanghae Province placed first in Yut-game, those of the Namap Co-op Farm in Yomju County, North Phyongan Province in Korean wrestling, those of the Ryongyon Co-op Farm in Anju City, South Phyongan Province in Taekwon-Do and those of the Sinam Co-op Farm in Ryongchon County, North Phyongan Province in swinging and seesaw. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A closing ceremony was addressed by Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citations, victory banners, medals and prizes were awarded to excellent teams and players at the closing ceremony.

U.S. Ranking Officials' Sophism Flailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- High-ranking officials of the Bush administration are recently describing "war on terrorism", an offspring of their war policy, as an "anti-fascist war" and branding members of Islamic resistance organizations as "Islamic fascists".
 Commenting on this, a Minju Joson analyst Tuesday dismisses the Bush administration's zealous beautification of its war policy with absurd phraseology as sophism of those driven to a tight corner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congressional off-year election between the Republican Party and the Democratic Party is due in November in the United States. The election will be a theater of judgment on the policy of the Bush administration and the Republican Party.  And the present situation is turning very unfavorable to the Bush administration and the Republican Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The public at home and abroad is becoming increasingly critical of the Bush administration's foreign policy and there is a growing pressure on it to stop the war and on the responsible politicians to resign. Such social atmosphere has led to a drastic drop in the support rate for the president and the administration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that if this trend is left to go on, the administration and the Republican Party will suffer a crushing defeat in the upcoming off-year election. Top brasses of the Bush administration, much upset by this, are trying to pull the wool over the eyes of the people with such words as "fascism". They must have seen that there would be no other way out but to beautify their war policy, soft-pedal public opinion opposed to it and keep pursuing military strong-arm policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should clearly understand what a miserable end its anachronistic policy will entail.

S. Korean Organizations Demand Building of Park for People at Site of U.S. Military Base
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Eighteen civic and environmental organizations of south Korea including the Citizens' Solidarity for Democratic Society and the Environmental Movement Association reportedly held a press conference in Seoul on Sept. 7, at which they declared a solidarity struggle for a stop to the scheme of the "government" authorities to institute "a special law on Ryongsan park."
 The south Korean authorities are now intending to institute "a special law on the creation of the Ryongsan national and historic park and readjustment of its surrounding area" (special law on Ryongsan park) for the purpose of covering the expenses for the transfer of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan by selling off the land of the base to entrepreneurs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations declared they would wage a solidarity struggle to force the authorities to drop the scheme and build a park for the people at the site of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan and use the U.S. military bases lying scattered in Seoul as auxiliary set-ups of the park and land for public use. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The press conference was followed by an inaugural ceremony of the Citizens Solidarity for Turning U.S. Military Base in Ryongsan into Ecological Park.

Full Play to Advantages of Korean-Style Socialism Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Collectivism represents the true picture of Korean-style socialism and the way of living of the Korean people. This socialism has won one victory after another despite unprecedentedly hard and complicated trials because it is strictly based on collectivism. Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The advantages of Korean-style socialism based on collectivism lie in that the headquarters of the revolution, the Workers' Party of Korea, the army and people form an integral whole and all fields are making steady progress thanks to such motive force as the creative energies of the whole army and all the people united on the basis of true comradeship. One of the great advantages of Korean-style socialism based on collectivism lies in that all people enjoy a worthy and happy life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Individual interests tally with those of the collective in a socialist society and individual interests are reflected in the interests of the collective. Under socialism not only the interests of the collective but individual interests are respected and utmost care is shown for all people. This is one of the important advantages of socialism in which the principle of collectivism is strictly observed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the people are fully enjoying an independent and creative life in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warm and deep care of the Party and the leader reach everywhere in the country and all people help and lead each other along like a big harmonious socialist family. This is the cradle where everyone can bring his hope and talent into full bloom. Ordinary working people and their sons and daughters are becoming heroes, intellectuals glorifying the honor of the country in the international arena and officials commanding the revolution under the care of the Party and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The period of the "Arduous March" provided the people with an opportunity to keenly realize what great benefits they received from the state in the past. Even in this difficult period, the Party and the state invariably enforced free education and free medical service for the people and made utmost efforts to provide them with stable living conditions. The standard of people's living is improving as the days go by as the building of a great prosperous powerful nation makes progress under the Songun leadership of the Party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no future under capitalism based on individualism but the prospect of Korean-style socialism is very bright.

9th National Exhibition of Inventions and New Technology under Way
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The 9th National Exhibition of Inventions and New Technology which opened at the Three-Revolution Exhibition in the DPRK on September 6 is going on till the 15th.
 More than 1,500 pieces of inventions and new technologies achieved by scientists and technicians of over 50 units of ministries, national institutions and industrial establishments are exhibited there. Some of the exhibits are actual things and others are on display in the form of diagram and software. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new kind of highly efficient impulse turbine, a support program for operation of electric power systems and others presented by the Ministry of Electricity and Coal Industries are drawing attention of the visitors as they have been proved successful in production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Ministry of Machine-Building Industry has put on exhibition a digital vertical comprehensive processing lathe and a gas nitrification process by compound accelerant, which are of great significance in development of machine-building industry of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A new kind of floodgate invented by scientists and technicians of the Ryongnam Ship Repair Yard marks a fresh advance in dock construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Catching eyes of the visitors is electron beam welding machine. It can be widely applied as it less deforms things while welding and ensures mechanical strength fully.
 Diagnostic reagent for antigen of epidemic hepatitis, a new kind of Taq DNA polymerase and medical ��-type gypseous bandage presented by the Institute of Medical Biology under the Academy of Medical Science, Pyongyang University of Medicine and Chollima County People's Hospital in South Phyongan Province are appreciated as good ones in diagnosis and medical treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition shows the scientific and technical achievements made thanks to the government's policy of paying importance to science and technology.

Social Being Expounded by Juche Idea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The Juche Idea clarifies that man is the social being.
 The term "social being" by the Juche idea defines the essential characteristics of man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It means that people form a social group and live and act in social relationship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having the social relationship, people make up a collective and live and conduct activities in society. Unthinkable apart from the social relations are a social collective and social life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Man is not isolated but belongs to a social collective. And he lives and acts as a member of society and collective, helping each other ahead. It is none other than the man who maintains and develops his own existence through the social cooperative relation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Man maintains and develops his existence in the course of establishing social relations and transforming the world purposefully and consciously. Herein lies the important feature of man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But, the preceding theories did not view man as the only social being but included the material conditions and economic relations of man's social life to social beings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-mentioned material conditions and economic relations are social ones which do not exist in nature. They are nothing but relations and creatures which come into being in the course of people forming a social collective and living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Man is the very social being who creates and enjoys the social wealth and establishes and transforms the social relations.

Talks between DPRK SPA Delegation and Parliamentary Delegation of Indonesia Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Talks between the delegation of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the parliamentary delegation of Indonesia were held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Tuesday.
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on the issue of boosting the relations between the two parliaments at a time when the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and Indonesia are favorably developing in different domains and on a series of issues of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present from the DPRK side were Kim Wan Su, chairman of the DPRK-Indonesia Friendship Parliamentary Group and deputy to the SPA, Kim Kwang Chol and Kim Song Hui, deputies to the SPA, and officials concerned, and from the Indonesian side members of the Indonesian parliamentary delegation headed by Yoseph Umarhadi, chairman of the Indonesia-DPRK Friendship Parliamentary Group, and Bambang Irawan K., charge d' affaires ad interim of the Indonesian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.
